div.p:
Of Subjects. O my God, give grace to me and all my fellow-subjects, next to thy own infinite self, to love and honour, to fear and obey our Sovereign Lord the King, thy own Vicegerent, for Conscience sake
Rom. 13.1, &c. 1 Pet. 2.13. Tit. 3.1., and for thy own sake, who hast placed Him over us;
O may we ever faithfully render Him his due tribute; O may we ever pray for His prosperity, sacrifice our fortunes and our lives in His defence, and be always ready rather to suffer than resist.

Lord, give me Grace to search every secret of my Heart, to leave no sin, if possible, unrepented of; 
                  •
               ill my Eyes full of Tears of Love, that with those Tears I may lament, all the Indignities I have offered thy Love.
